data.database_description: The database is designed to manage and track customer interactions, sales orders, financial transactions, and product details for an e-commerce platform. It records customer information, including personal details and contact information, in the `Customers` table. The `Orders`, `Order_Items`, and `Invoices` tables facilitate tracking of purchase orders, individual products within those orders, and the billing process, respectively. Financial interactions are captured through the `Financial_Transactions` and `Accounts` tables, which link transactions to customer accounts and invoices. Products and their categories are organized in the `Products` and `Product_Categories` tables, ensuring proper classification and pricing details. Together, these tables enable comprehensive management of customer relations, sales processing, financial oversight, and product inventory.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each customer.
First name of the customer.
Middle initial of the customer, if available.
Last name of the customer.
Gender identifier for the customer (e.g., '1' for male, '0' for female).
Email address used for communication with the customer.
Username used by the customer to log into the platform.
Encrypted password associated with the customer's login credentials.
Contact phone number of the customer.
City or town where the customer resides.
State, county, or province of the customer's residence.
Country of the customer's residence.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores personal and contact information for customers interacting with the e-commerce platform.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each order.
References the customer who placed the order.
Timestamp indicating when the order was placed.
Description or summary of the order contents.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks purchase orders placed by customers.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each invoice generated for a customer's purchase.
References the order being invoiced.
Date and time when the invoice was issued.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks invoices generated for orders, linking them to their respective dates.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each account.
References the customer who owns the account.
Date and time when the account was opened.
Name or identifier for the account, potentially used for reference purposes.
Additional details about the account, such as status or category (e.g., Regular, VIP).

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records financial accounts associated with customers, including account details and status.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each product category.
Description of the product type or category.
Value Added Tax rate applicable to the product category.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores product categories, their descriptions, and VAT ratings.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each product listed in the catalog.
Identifier of the parent product if applicable (for variations or sub-products).
Foreign key linking to Product_Categories for category identification.
Price per unit of the product.
Name of the product.
Color specification of the product.
Size specification of the product.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about products, including pricing and categorization.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each financial transaction.
References the account involved in the transaction.
Identifier linking the transaction to a specific invoice.
Type of financial interaction, e.g., Payment or Refund.
Date when the financial transaction occurred.
Monetary value of the transaction.
Additional remarks about the transaction.
Extra details related to the transaction.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records financial interactions linked to customer accounts and invoices.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each item within an order, used to track specific products in the sales pipeline.
Identifier linking the order item to its respective order.
Identifier linking the order item to a specific product.
Quantity of the product ordered in this particular order item.
Additional details regarding the order item, such as specifications or notes.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Details individual products within each order.

columns.columnDescription: References the unique ID of an order item in the Order_Items table.
Unique identifier for the invoice to which this line item belongs, linking it to the Invoices table.
Identifier for the product sold, linked to the Products table.
The name or title of the product being sold in the transaction.
Number of units of the product included in this particular invoice line item.
Unit price of the product at the time of sale, before any taxes or discounts.
Calculated cost of the products based on factors such as pricing strategy and possibly including any discounts applied.
The calculated VAT amount payable for this line item, determined by applying the relevant tax rate to the product's price.
Total cost of the line item, including the base product cost and applicable taxes or other charges.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks individual line items within invoices, detailing product specifics and associated financial metrics for each item sold.
